parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, including the radio, air conditioning, and turn signals, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The radio turns off or malfunctions
the air conditioning unit becomes inoperable
the turn signal sounds are inaudible
the speedometer turns black
the low oil pressure warning light is illuminated
the instrument panel lights flicker
the blower motor activates independently
and the vehicle stalls or loses electrical power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose electrical power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses electrical power
the "Engine Reduce Power" and "Ignition Switch Failure" messages are displayed
the check engine warning light is illuminated
and the vehicle is unable to run smoothly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaking into the trunk can cause electrical components to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Water leaks into the trunk during inclement weather
a message regarding theft is displayed
and the ignition key is stuck in the ignition switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates out of control
the engine is racing
and the brakes are unable to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The power steering warning indicator illuminates
the steering wheel seizes or becomes hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the power steering assist fails
the vehicle is difficult to control
and the steering wheel locks or becomes stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the loss of steering control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering column comes loose or falls apart
the steering wheel seizes or becomes hard to turn
the steering wheel locks or becomes stuck
and the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The uncommanded turning of the vehicle can cause the loss of vehicle control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle makes an uncommanded turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the traction control light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radio and infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents, and may also affect the functionality of other vehicle systems, such as heating and air conditioning.
symptoms: The radio turns on and off randomly
the radio flickers on and off
disrupting music and heating/cooling system
the radio system requires rebooting
and the radio
dash lights
and climate control panel flash on and off with a popping sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Heating and Air Conditioning System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heating and air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, leading to accidents, and may also cause water damage and corrosion in the vehicle.
symptoms: The air conditioning blows hot air
the heating system blows cold air
the air conditioning and heating system turn on and off intermittently
the passenger floorboard is saturated with water
and the heater core leaks antifreeze.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Convertible Top and Water Leak Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the convertible top and water leak issues can cause water damage and corrosion in the vehicle, leading to electrical system failures and accidents.
symptoms: The rear bow on the convertible top bends
causing the roof to not properly close
and water leaks into the rear floor pan.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly replace recalled keys can cause safety risks and inconvenience to vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealerships charge for key replacement
despite the recall
and owners are left with faulty keys that can cause safety issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and timing chain can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, and may also cause costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly dies without warning
the car loses compression
and the timing chain breaks.
